.TH "GamepadButton.value" "JS" "February 5, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
GamepadButton.value \- GamepadButton: value property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]GamepadButton.value\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]GamepadButton\f[R] interface returns a double value used to
represent the current state of analog buttons on many modern gamepads,
such as the triggers.
.PP
The values are normalized to the range \f[CR]0.0\f[R] \[em]
\f[CR]1.0\f[R], with \f[CR]0.0\f[R] representing a button that is not
pressed, and 1.0 representing a button that is fully pressed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]let\f[R] gp = navigator.getGamepads()[0];

\f[B]if\f[R] (gp.buttons[0].value > 0) {
  \f[I]// respond to analog button being pressed in\f[R]
}
.EE
.SH VALUE
A double.
